WEBVTT

00:01.134 --> 00:03.585
♪♪

00:06.339 --> 00:10.398
<i>♪♪</i>

00:12.283 --> 00:14.682
Officer Mailer. Leona.

00:15.085 --> 00:17.236
Harley Carter. Vijay Gill.

00:17.541 --> 00:19.799
Here to see Detective Sam Shaw.

00:19.824 --> 00:20.957
She expecting you?

00:20.982 --> 00:22.732
Well, she's usually
one step ahead of me,

00:22.781 --> 00:24.424
so, yeah, she probably is.

00:24.839 --> 00:26.719
You know what? We'll
just let ourselves in.

00:26.838 --> 00:28.017
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

00:28.116 --> 00:30.353
Uh, no. Excuse me, Mr. Carter.

00:30.378 --> 00:32.119
No civilians allowed past this point.

00:32.145 --> 00:34.399
I'm not sure if I'd call me a civilian.

00:34.439 --> 00:36.390
I mean, I am a regular guy.
Blah, blah, blah.

00:36.415 --> 00:40.301
But, uh... I did help you guys
crack a pretty big case recently.

00:40.738 --> 00:43.151
We get assistance from many
people in the community.

00:43.371 --> 00:45.827
Ooh. Okay, I'm sorry. "Get assistance?"

00:46.098 --> 00:48.561
Uh, Mr. Carter here cracked
that case wide open.

00:48.586 --> 00:51.007
And now, your mayor is asking
him to join the police force.

00:51.032 --> 00:54.233
Easy, big guy, easy.
I've been asked to consult,

00:54.258 --> 00:56.026
officially asked to consult.

00:56.051 --> 00:57.893
I'm sure the whole station
is buzzing about it.

01:01.842 --> 01:05.831
Okay, um, you know what?
Why don't you just ask Sam

01:05.856 --> 01:07.387
if we can take her to lunch?

01:07.578 --> 01:08.937
I'll see if I can track her down.

01:09.125 --> 01:10.164
Thanks.

01:11.309 --> 01:13.250
Can we talk about Bobby Sobelman?

01:13.445 --> 01:15.021
Please don't tell me this is about

01:15.046 --> 01:16.299
his son's bar mitzvah again.

01:16.324 --> 01:17.901
Yeah, he'd really like you to be there.

01:17.926 --> 01:19.690
I'm not flying all the way to LA

01:19.793 --> 01:22.276
just to kiss the butt of the
head of the studio, okay?

01:22.310 --> 01:24.352
Plus, his son is, like, super weird.

01:24.386 --> 01:26.057
Every time I see him, he yells "candy!"

01:26.082 --> 01:28.506
And then jams his hand in my pocket,
starts fishing around.

01:28.531 --> 01:29.556
It's totally inappropriate.

01:29.580 --> 01:32.071
Okay, look, you know this is
not about the bar mitzvah, right?

01:32.346 --> 01:33.383
Bobby is worried

01:33.408 --> 01:36.211
that you're going to spend your whole
hiatus up here and not come back.

01:36.325 --> 01:38.136
He just wants to hear
from you, face to face,

01:38.161 --> 01:39.933
that you are committed to <i>Call Carter.</i>

01:39.958 --> 01:42.004
I'm committed, okay?
We don't have to seal the deal

01:42.029 --> 01:45.226
by letting some 13-year-old
kid jam his hand down my pants.

01:47.724 --> 01:50.279
Oh, uh, that's a... that's a euphemism,

01:50.304 --> 01:52.006
like, Hollywood euphemism.

01:53.106 --> 01:55.556
You're coming back, right?
After the hiatus?

01:56.423 --> 01:57.939
Sure. Probably.

01:58.018 --> 01:59.287
You have no idea how alarming

01:59.320 --> 02:00.881
the word "probably" is to me right now.

02:01.025 --> 02:02.142
I'm coming back.

02:02.888 --> 02:05.365
Yeah, you didn't say "probably"
that time, but I heard it.

02:05.685 --> 02:07.694
You're going to take the
mayor's offer, aren't you?

02:07.898 --> 02:09.115
I have to talk to Sam first.

02:09.199 --> 02:11.371
Okay, great. That is a great idea.

02:11.396 --> 02:13.685
But how do I talk to Bobby Sobelman?

02:14.146 --> 02:15.895
I don't know. Figure it out, okay?

02:15.920 --> 02:18.089
That's why you're paid
the medium sized bucks.

02:18.793 --> 02:20.200
- Wow.
- What are you doing here?

02:20.562 --> 02:22.546
I was going to take you out to lunch

02:22.571 --> 02:25.052
and Vijay is going to drive us.

02:25.271 --> 02:26.544
Hey, Detective Shaw.

02:26.569 --> 02:28.772
Hi, Vijay. Well, you should
have called. I have a thing.

02:28.913 --> 02:31.551
A thing? What do you have
a date or something?

02:32.597 --> 02:34.329
Not something. You have a date.

02:34.354 --> 02:36.305
No, a good friend of
mine is getting an EMTy.

02:36.409 --> 02:38.482
- An empty what?
- No, an EMTy.

02:38.507 --> 02:40.841
An EMT, Emergency Medical
Technician Award.

02:40.866 --> 02:42.526
It's actually a bit of a deal, an EMTy.

02:42.573 --> 02:44.691
Yeah, that name is really
working against them.

02:45.002 --> 02:46.479
(CHUCKLING) All right.

02:47.698 --> 02:49.222
Um, how about dinner?

02:49.306 --> 02:52.308
We could talk about your
latest cases, swap theories.

02:52.693 --> 02:56.587
I'd also love to talk to you
about this offer from the Mayor.

02:57.017 --> 02:58.056
Hold it. You're not...

02:58.364 --> 03:00.493
you're not thinking of taking
her up on that, are you?

03:00.907 --> 03:03.261
Well, I want to talk
to you about it first.

03:03.871 --> 03:06.627
Okay, yeah. Uh, we
definitely need to talk,

03:06.660 --> 03:08.108
but I can't right now. I gotta go.

03:08.192 --> 03:09.284
Okay? Call me.

03:10.385 --> 03:12.417
Hey, how about I use
those medium-sized bucks

03:12.450 --> 03:13.487
and buy you lunch?

03:13.810 --> 03:15.526
Yeah. Let's get out of here.

03:16.267 --> 03:17.290
Okay.

03:17.334 --> 03:18.378
(PAPARAZZI CHATTERING)

03:18.403 --> 03:19.946
Okay, all right. Hey, come on, come on.

03:19.970 --> 03:22.225
All right, hey, this
isn't the time, guys.

03:22.250 --> 03:25.183
Thank you. Welcome to Bishop.
Welcome to Bishop.

03:25.671 --> 03:27.045
Was not expecting that.

03:27.070 --> 03:28.603
(EXHALING SHARPLY) How
does my hair look?

03:28.627 --> 03:30.359
- Oh, perfect. Ten out of ten.
- Yeah? You sure?

03:30.383 --> 03:31.937
Yep. You have a nice glisten.

03:32.139 --> 03:33.660
Yeah. I feel a little sweaty.
Am I too sweaty?

03:33.684 --> 03:34.959
Uh-uh. Just the right amount.

03:34.984 --> 03:36.296
HALEY: All right,
we've gotta check those pics...

03:36.320 --> 03:37.361
Detective Carter?

03:37.386 --> 03:38.886
Ooh. Okay, it's always
great to meet a fan,

03:38.910 --> 03:40.642
but Mister... not detective...

03:40.667 --> 03:41.872
I'm so sorry. I'm late for a thing

03:41.896 --> 03:44.261
- with somebody. I'm sorry.
- Well why don't you write to us

03:44.286 --> 03:46.015
and then we'll write to you,
like they used to do?

03:46.039 --> 03:48.041
Wait, wait. Please, please, look.
I have something for you.

03:48.065 --> 03:49.282
Sorry. Sorry.

03:49.387 --> 03:50.696
Detective Carter, please.

